Description: Body sherd of East Greek grey ware large pottery vessel, probably a krater or dinos; dark grey fabric core sandwiched between pale brown margins, with mica inclusions; dark slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Joins British Museum 1965,0930.408 and probably belongs to the same vessel as British Museum 1965,0930.406; 1965,0930.407; 1965;0930.409; 1965,0930.410.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.057)
